# The [[killing]] or [[euthanasia]] of the [[elderly]]
#*'''2000''', Michael Brogden & Preeti Nijhar, ''[http://books.google.com/books?id=NWop1wdCMhQC&pg=PA33&dq=Geronticide&sig=Pw54KqIcZ4epgxVVGhR-gxaz0Do Crime, Abuse and the Elderly]'', p. 33.
#*:Maxwell et al. (1982) studied '''geronticide''' practices in some ninety-five different societies.
The Inuit, hunters of the Arctic region, commit geronticide when they leave the elderly that have become too infirm to keep up and contribute to household survival behind, resulting in their death, (Nowak, B., & Laird, P. (2010). Cultural anthropology. San Diego, Bridgepoint Education, Inc. https://content.ashford.edu).